        <p class="lead">
          Business owners in Ahmedabad come to us with quotes ranging from Rs 8,000 to Rs 3,00,000 for what appears to be the same thing: a professional business website. Both quotes can be legitimate. Both can also be terrible value. The difference lies entirely in what is included, how it is built, and whether the finished product will actually serve your business goals. This guide breaks down honest pricing for every category of website in India in 2026.
        </p>

        <h2 id="why-website-pricing-in-india-varies-so-much">Why website pricing in India varies so much</h2>
        <p>
          A freelancer working from home in a Tier-3 city with low overheads can profitably build a template-based WordPress site for Rs 8,000. A web design agency in Ahmedabad with designers, developers, project managers, and proper quality assurance processes cannot. Neither is dishonest. They are delivering fundamentally different products.
        </p>
        <p>
          The problem is that both of these are often described to clients as "a professional business website." Understanding what actually goes into the production of a website, and what the difference is between a Rs 10,000 and a Rs 1,00,000 site, helps you make an informed choice rather than simply choosing the cheapest quote.
        </p>

        <h2 id="web-design-price-tiers-india-2026">Web design price tiers in India 2026</h2>

        <h3 id="rs-5000-to-rs-20000">Rs 5,000 to Rs 20,000: Template sites and basic builds</h3>
        <p>
          At this price point, you are getting a pre-built template with your content, logo, and colours applied. The template may be a free or low-cost WordPress theme, a Wix site, or similar. The work involved is primarily content entry and basic customisation, not design or development.
        </p>
        <p>
          This option is appropriate for: very new businesses with no budget that need basic online presence, landing pages for specific campaigns, simple brochure sites for businesses where the website is not a primary source of leads. It is not appropriate for businesses where the website is expected to generate enquiries, rank on Google, or represent a professional brand.
        </p>
        <p>
          Common issues at this price point: no SEO optimisation, poor mobile experience, very slow page speed, generic appearance that does not differentiate you from competitors, and no support after delivery.
        </p>

        <h3 id="rs-20000-to-rs-60000">Rs 20,000 to Rs 60,000: Small business websites</h3>
        <p>
          This is the most common price range for small business websites in Ahmedabad. A good agency or freelancer at this price point should deliver a custom-designed website built on WordPress or a similar CMS, mobile-responsive across all devices, basic on-page SEO setup, a contact form with proper email delivery, and a reasonable page speed score.
        </p>
        <p>
          DC technolabs' small business website packages start in this range. What distinguishes a good delivery from a poor one at this price point is whether the design is genuinely custom-built around your business or simply a template with your content dropped in, and whether SEO fundamentals are baked in from the start.
        </p>
        <p>
          Questions to ask at this price tier: Will the design be custom or template-based? What PageSpeed score can you target? What SEO elements are included? What support is available after launch? Who hosts the site and who controls the domain?
        </p>

        <h3 id="rs-60000-to-rs-1-50000">Rs 60,000 to Rs 1,50,000: Professional business websites</h3>
        <p>
          At this price point you should expect a genuinely custom design process including wireframing, brand-consistent design, and multiple revision rounds. Development should include conversion-optimised page layouts, proper technical SEO setup, Google Analytics and Search Console integration, site speed optimisation to 90+ PageSpeed scores, and structured data markup.
        </p>
        <p>
          This tier is appropriate for established businesses where the website is an important sales and marketing asset, service businesses competing for local search visibility in Ahmedabad, and companies that want a site that positions them professionally against larger competitors.
        </p>

        <h3 id="rs-1-50000-to-rs-5-00000">Rs 1,50,000 to Rs 5,00,000: E-commerce and complex sites</h3>
        <p>
          E-commerce sites require significantly more work than brochure websites. A proper e-commerce build in India includes product catalogue design, shopping cart and checkout integration, Indian payment gateway setup (Razorpay, PayU, or similar), GST-compliant invoicing, inventory management integration, and logistics API connections.
        </p>
        <p>
          At the lower end of this range (Rs 1,50,000 to Rs 2,50,000) you can build a solid Shopify or WooCommerce store for a small to mid-sized catalogue. At the higher end, you are looking at custom e-commerce builds with complex product configurators, multi-vendor marketplaces, or enterprise inventory integrations.
        </p>

        <h3 id="above-rs-5-00000">Above Rs 5,00,000: Custom web applications</h3>
        <p>
          Custom web applications, SaaS platforms, patient management systems, dealer portals, and similar projects involve software development, not just web design. Projects in this range require proper technical architecture, database design, API development, security auditing, and ongoing maintenance contracts. If a vendor quotes Rs 5,00,000+ for a standard business website without complex functionality, they are overcharging.
        </p>

